me.id: This is a language ID. It should be different for each file
me.native: The name of a language, in this particular language.
me.eng: The name of a language, in English

common.apply: Usually in modal dialogues, in the meaning "to apply a change", "apply settings"
common.copy: A verb, "to create a duplicate" (not a ct.js Copy!).
common.search: Shown next to a search field

intro.boosty: Boosty is a service, similar to Patreon.
welcomeHeaders:
Here and below you may replace any unknown in your language phrases with funny quotes you would instead prefer.

A greetings gesture from StarTrek, aka "vulkan" gesture. You should probably leave this field as is.

intro.authorBy: "$1" gets replaced with the author's name.

modules.help: As a documentation page that has all the methods and properties described
modules.logs: A title of a tab that shows a changelof of a module, when clicked. It can be shorter than modules.log2
modules.logs2: A title for a changelog of a module.
modules.filter: A noun; a title of the collapsible section with a filtering form inside it

docsPanel.reference: A document with all the properties and methods described in it

main.heading: The heading of the settings section with main project settings
main.miscHeading: The heading of the settings section with project settings that did not fit into other groups

copyProperties.multipleValues: Describes multiple values of one property

roomView.simulate: Can also be called "Simulation". Describes a mode during which sprites and backgrounds animate.
roomView.changeGridSize: A command that changes grid's size
roomView.xrayMode: A mode that makes everything see-through

tools.select: As a tool for selecting stuff

roomView.resetView: Running this command brings camera back to the center of the room, and resets zoom

styleView.useCustomFont: Can be worded differently to become shorter; this is a label of a button that opens a dialog with imported TTF fonts.
styleView.testText: It is recommended that you include both a string in your language and in English, as it will help with picking fonts that have multilingual support.

charsets.custom: Describing a custom set of symbols

templateView.defaultCount: A label for a field that sets how many sprites are shown when no value has been set through code.

coreEventsCategories.input: A name of an event when someone inputs something into a text field

catnip.changeBlockTo: $1 will be replaced with the name of a block in context menus

blockNames.this: As a JavaScript keyword. If translation is complicated, you can use "I" or "me" instead of  "this".
blockNames.get x: Probably doesn't need translation at all.
blockNames.get y: Probably doesn't need translation at all.

blockDisplayNames.x of: As in a sentence "get X of a copy"
blockDisplayNames.y of: As in sentence "get Y of a copy"

blockLabels.toWrite: A preposition used when referring to something we write to
blockLabels.fromRead: A preposition used when referring to something we read from
blockLabels.atPosition: A preposition used when referring to something placed at position
blockLabels.forDuring: A preposition used when referring to something happening for a specific duration
blockLabels.toDestination: A preposition used when referring to a place, to a destination
